subSubSection.paragraph:
The additionally studied male specimen from Brazil (
Parana
) differs from the holotype in its larger body size (9 mm), slightly smoky wings, and the presence of a pair of submedian vittae of black pile on tergite 4. Possibly, this specimen belongs to another species, which is why it is not designated as paratype. However, the number of available specimens is too low to make a decision on this.
